HEADWORD: Diamide
<hw>Di*am"ide</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>amide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any
compound containing two amido groups united with one or more acid or
negative radicals, -- as distinguished from a diamine. Cf. <xex>Amido
acid</xex>, under <er>Amido</er>, and <xex>Acid amide</xex>, under
<er>Amide</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diamido-</ent>⟦br⟧
